result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Corbin James Nelson

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Corbin James Nelson in court with attorney Tina M. Abernethy-Mays.  Defendant Corbin James Nelson in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF245 and 16CF79 @ 1:56 p.m. Waiver of preliminary examination filed for both. Court reviews with Def. Court finds waivers knowing and voluntary, finds probable cause and binds over. Informations filed. Copies received, reading waived. 16CF79 reserve all juris. obj. and enter not guilty pleas on cts 1-8. Court receives not guilty pleas. Agreement 15CF245 Def will plead to cts 1 & 4, remaining cts and all cts in  15CM249 and 16CF35 dismiss and read in. On both cts. withheld sentence, 4 yrs probation, AODA, complete all follow through treatment. Court costs. DNA sample and surcharge. Atty Abernethy-Mays and Def agree. Court formally calls and gives same appearances for 15CM249 and 16CF35. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to ct 1 15CF245 - no contest. Plea to ct 4 - no contest. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in 15CF245 cts 2, 3 & 5, 15CM249 cts 1 & 2, 16CF35 cts 1-4. State now asks that 16CF35 be dismissed outright for reason stated. Court grants, 16CF35 dismissed outright. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Abernethy-Mays satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CF245 ct 1 possess meth and ct 4 felony bail jumping. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court, will follow agreement. Ct 1 sentence withheld, 4 yrs probation, AODA and complete any follow through and any counseling deemed appropriate, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.  34 days credit if revoked. Ct 4 sentence withheld, 4 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, court costs, DNA surcharge, 34 days credit if revoked. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Discussion on bond. Bond in 15CF245 to be applied, return any balance to poster. Bond in 16CF35 return to poster. Postconviction rights. Off the record briefly. Back on the record. 16CF79 - Bond arguments by Atty Abernethy-Mays. Response by State. Court orders $1,500 signature bond. Status conference 08/01/16 @ 3:30 p.m.
